title: For Sale:  AR-15 Lightweight Build
postcontent: $2000 OBO  This is a side-charging, lightweight AR-15 build constructed with the highest grade of parts and accessories. The American Spirit Arms upper receiver is mated with a Daniel Defense Lightweight 16 inch 1:7 twist barrel capped with a Lantac Dragon muzzle break. The tan ADM QD scope mount, holding a Vortex 1-4x24 TMCQ MOA, looks at home with the tan Troy Alpha rail and the GWACS polymer lower. A very smooth two-stage trigger is accompanied by a Battle Arms Ambidextrous 45degree safety selector. The gun comes with one tan Magpul 30rd PMag. This AR has been shot about 100 times with various 223Rem and 5.56mm ammunitions, ranging from 45gr to 69gr without any issues. For three shots from cold-bore it is a 1inch gun at 100 yards (with 55gr PMC). The gun comes with Magpul BUIS and weighs 5.5 pounds empty without the optic and mount. To fit the billet upper receiver the polymer lower did have to be filed down in certain areas as it is designed for a standard receiver; this work is noticeable when the rifle is pulled apart for cleaning if one looks closely but in no way impedes the operation or the external looks of the rifle. The finish on the takedown pins is noticeably worn; to my knowledge this is related to a bad batch of pins (in reference to their finish) GWACS had a while back. The only work that is recommended and has not been done is staking the low profile gas block and adding a JP Enterprises silent-captured recoil spring. I will cover shipping and transfer costs on my end; transfer fees posed by the receiving FFL will not be covered by myself. Cash or bank transfer only; face-to-face meetings welcome. $2000 OBO

title: For Sale:  5.56mm / .223 M-856 62gr. Tracer Rounds RED LONG RANGE/ steel penetrator
postcontent:
Up for sale is 960 M856 62 grain tracers. These are the mating rounds that go with the M855 green tip steel cone tipped penatrator rounds.  The M856 round, is usually mixed in with M855 on a belt in a four to one ratio for belt fed firearms.  These have the steel cone in thee nose, just like the M855 rounds and are magnetic. 

The M856 tracer is a long range tracer good to about 900 yards, and are red in color. I have had 100% reliability in the round lighting off....yes, 100% ! Some of the older tracer rounds you can find, your lucky to get 25%-50% to light.  

Take the whole lot, or let me know how many you want.

.42 cents a round  or 400 bucks for the whole lot of 960 rounds. I will entertain some offers, but be advised, this is a GREAT price for this specialty ammo. Some of the orange painted tips will be slightly missing from some of the projectiles, but 95% of the paint is there for the most part.



call or text
270-844-three one nine nine

title: For Sale:  5.56mm / .223 M-856 62gr. Tracer Rounds RED LONG RANGE/ steel penetrator
postcontent:
Up for sale is 960 M856 62 grain tracers. These are the mating rounds that go with the M855 green tip steel cone tipped penatrator rounds.  The M856 round, is usually mixed in with M855 on a belt in a four to one ratio for belt fed firearms.  These have the steel cone in thee nose, just like the M855 rounds and are magnetic. 

The M856 tracer is a long range tracer good to about 900 yards, and are red in color. I have had 100% reliability in the round lighting off....yes, 100% ! Some of the older tracer rounds you can find, your lucky to get 25%-50% to light.  

Take the whole lot, or let me know how many you want.

.42 cents a round  or 400 bucks for the whole lot of 960 rounds. I will entertain some offers, but be advised, this is a GREAT price for this specialty ammo. Some of the orange painted tips will be slightly missing from some of the projectiles, but 95% of the paint is there for the most part.
